The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, July 09, 2003 				 Less red tape in gear deals 
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, July 8: In a move to bring about transparency in the procurement of equipment by Bharat Sanchar Nigam Ltd and Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Ltd and to give impetus to the telecom equipment manufacturers, the government has cut down the tendering process from 180 days to 120 days and has decided not to change the eligibility criteria once the tender is awarded. 
